3.4

I got a pretty high R square of 0.9371 which means the model did great on capturing the relationhship between price carat and cut

3.5

The intercept coefficient means that when the fair cut diamond is 1 carat \(e^0\) the price of it would be \(e^{8.2}\). The log(carat) coefficient means that when you increase the log(carat) of a diamond by one the price of it would be increased by \(e^{1.69}\) percent. The cutGood coefficient means that when you get two diamond of same carat, the good cut one would be 0.163245 percent more expensive than the fair cut one. The cutIdeal coefficient means that when you get two diamond of same carat, the ideal cut one would be 0.317212 percent more expensive than the fair cut one. The cutPremium coefficient means that when you get two diamond of same carat, the Premium cut one would be 0.238217 percent more expensive than the fair cut one. The cutVery Good coefficient means that when you get two diamond of same carat, the Premium cut one would be 0.240753 percent more expensive than the fair cut one.
